  </p>
  <h2 id="module">Module Development</h2>
  <p>
    Most custom module development can be created by advertising configuration via YML files from a drupal module.

  </p>
  <p><strong>Sample contents of module_name.forena.yml file:</strong></p>
  <pre>
  # Advertise a report directory to forena.
  report directory: reports

  # The data section advertises custom sql.
  data:

    # This establishes a data block location for custorm drupal data blocks (e.g. frx:block="mydata/foo")
    mydata:
      driver: FrxDrupal
      title: Drupal Core Data
      user callback: forena_current_user_uid
      source: data/drupal

  </pre>
